  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/877132172?book_show_action=true">Mar 09, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelli Smith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelli Smith" href="/user/show/16743439-kelli-smith">Kelli Smith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer877132172" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16436446524066908687">I am always so excited to read the next book in this series ! OL Ramos improves the whole package with each addition.<br/><br/>One of the things that I look forward to is the new and invigorating characters that are incorporated in each new book. I will have to say, that I was not disappointed. Father Vassilli is such an enigma and I adore his personality. The main characters,Michael, Liz, and Vincent are of course prominent, as well as Cain, Sariel, and Mary. There are some very descript demons, gods, an</span>
  <span id="freeText16436446524066908687" style="display:none">I am always so excited to read the next book in this series ! OL Ramos improves the whole package with each addition.<br /><br />One of the things that I look forward to is the new and invigorating characters that are incorporated in each new book. I will have to say, that I was not disappointed. Father Vassilli is such an enigma and I adore his personality. The main characters,Michael, Liz, and Vincent are of course prominent, as well as Cain, Sariel, and Mary. There are some very descript demons, gods, and goddesses that are brought forth in this book also. I really appreciate the time that this Author puts in to researching these folk lore creatures. Thank You !<br /><br />That brings me to the action scenes. I love reading these scenes because I feel like I am pulled right into the middle of the battle. I can read it and know where each character is and never lose track of what they are doing or what is happening. Ramos is great at "painting the whole picture."<br /><br />And finally, the romance. Ahhhh Liz and Vincent. The thing I love about this series is how each book gets more in depth with the relationship of these two characters. It's like listening to an Italian aria. The story begins and builds until you are so lost in this romance and before you know it, your heart is pounding and you are screaming at your Kindle ! Well done Mr. Ramos !<br /><br />Without posting any spoilers, I am going to say this. There are a couple of things happen that really threw me for a loop and left me shocked. I want to say more, but instead, I will encourage you to grab The Keeper: Awakening (Book 1) and start this incredible journey that OL Ramos has made a part of our lives.<br /><br />Bravo !</span>
  <a data-text-id="16436446524066908687" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


