<span id="freeTextContainer14793781532419329768">It&apos;s not all that common when we get a paranormal book that includes all the &apos;head&apos; honchos of paranormals. <br/>In this series we start with the vampires and werewolves, who are naturally not on each others good sides, but Michael and Vincent are the oddities. Then we have keepers, which if you&apos;ve read up to this point you know how important keepers are to the supers in this world. But now we&apos;re adding in Angels and Demons (ArchDemons at that!).<br/><br/>Just when you think our group will get to rest and star</span>
  <span id="freeText14793781532419329768" style="display:none">It's not all that common when we get a paranormal book that includes all the 'head' honchos of paranormals. <br />In this series we start with the vampires and werewolves, who are naturally not on each others good sides, but Michael and Vincent are the oddities. Then we have keepers, which if you've read up to this point you know how important keepers are to the supers in this world. But now we're adding in Angels and Demons (ArchDemons at that!).<br /><br />Just when you think our group will get to rest and start to enjoy building lives together another evil works it's way to the top. However, after Klein's death we learn he was basically a puppet for the real baddies that are determined wipe the Earth of those that would rebel against them. <br />Of all the books I've read so far, I honestly thought the third would forever be my favorite. However, Sanctuary has knocked Rebirth out of the field! I can't wait to see what we get next!</span>
