<div id="review_883252351" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/883252351" />
    <a title="Candy Golden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15977577-candy-golden"><img alt="Candy Golden" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1357071136p2/15977577.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/883252351?book_show_action=true">Mar 16, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Candy Golden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Candy Golden" href="/user/show/15977577-candy-golden">Candy Golden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer883252351" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12438270444308261554">Each book in this series just gets better and better and better. Seriously. As good as his last book in this series was, this book is even better. I just couldn&apos;t put it down. If you haven&apos;t yet started this series, Awakening (the first one) is free. <br/><br/>I had said that I had wanted more action, and boy did I get it. Not only did we get the main characters ie: Liz, Michael, Cain, Mary and Vincent, we also got a plethora of cast members thrown into the mix. <br/><br/>This series has everything. It&apos;s got vamps,</span>
  <span id="freeText12438270444308261554" style="display:none">Each book in this series just gets better and better and better. Seriously. As good as his last book in this series was, this book is even better. I just couldn't put it down. If you haven't yet started this series, Awakening (the first one) is free. <br /><br />I had said that I had wanted more action, and boy did I get it. Not only did we get the main characters ie: Liz, Michael, Cain, Mary and Vincent, we also got a plethora of cast members thrown into the mix. <br /><br />This series has everything. It's got vamps, angels, werewolves, witches, demons, hell hounds and more. It's also got life lessons along the way. Those lessons sucked me in and I actually FELT for the characters (and sometimes not in a good way). To me, the mark of a good author is when you can get sucked into the world that they are painting, whether it be the joy that they feel, the betrayal that they feel, and the anguish as well. When I can actually be disgusted by the actions of the characters in a story, then to me it's a VERY good book. I will have to say that I actually had tears in my eyes from time to time. <br /><br />Not going to get too much into the storyline with this review (the synopsis and other reviews can do that for you), but the way it made me FEEL. <br /><br />Kudos to Mr. Ramos for job WELL done. Bravo! </span>
  <a data-text-id="12438270444308261554" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


