<span id="freeTextContainer15986292222976619232">The Keeper: Sanctuary by O.L. Ramos is book 4 in the Keeper Series and it is amazing. The characters have grown stronger and closer together, staying true to their chosen mission. This addition adds new, delightful characters yet maintains the charm and relationships that I have become addicted to in the first three books. The writing is strong and consistent, which is terrific considering the vast number of additions. As a fan of a well written fight scene, the ones in this book are flawless. N</span>
  <span id="freeText15986292222976619232" style="display:none">The Keeper: Sanctuary by O.L. Ramos is book 4 in the Keeper Series and it is amazing. The characters have grown stronger and closer together, staying true to their chosen mission. This addition adds new, delightful characters yet maintains the charm and relationships that I have become addicted to in the first three books. The writing is strong and consistent, which is terrific considering the vast number of additions. As a fan of a well written fight scene, the ones in this book are flawless. Never do you lose track of any of the key players. The descriptions and story line are theater quality, creating images in my mind as surely as if I were watching it on screen. The love scenes are poetic and tender, even when acrobatic. This book is a must read, a productive addition to an amazing series. And the hook...oh the hook!</span>
